<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880419-0048 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief: Reliance Group Holdings Inc. </HL><SO> </SO><CO> REL ZNT </CO><IN> TNM INS </IN><TEXT>   Reliance Insurance Co. said it retained Shearson Lehman Hutton Inc. to find a buyer for its nearly six million shares, or 30.8%, of Zenith National Insurance Corp., Woodland Hills, Calif.    Reliance is a unit of New York investor Saul Steinberg's Reliance Group Holdings Inc.    In composite trading yesterday on the New York Stock Exchange, Zenith National shares rose $1 to close at $20.625, valuing Reliance's stake at about $123 million.    Reliance wouldn't say why it was selling its stake, which it began to acquire in 1981. The shares are beneficially owned by Reliance Financial Services Corp., also a unit of Reliance Group Holdings. </TEXT></DOC>